<tt>Sun Jun  8 14:06:23 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
To all,<br>
Before any new set of relations with Vietnam get rolling, the US needs to demand that all Amerasians (and their Vietnamese families) be allowed to leave Vietnam for the US it they so choose.  They (Amerasians) are literally American's sons and daughters and Vietnam's denial of free passage to many of them equates to nothing more than the illegal detaining of American citizens.<br><br>
The normalization of relations may be good for prompting the Vietnamese government to make more of an effort for accounting of our MIA/POW's, but I feel that as with everything else this government does, their is a <br>
money/profit issue at hand.  Vietnam has cheap labor and a good source of rubber.  I am not a conspiracy nut (you know big business running influencing the government), but what does companies like Coca Cola, Kodak and GoodYear stand to gain (I'm not trying to single this companies out, just making a point)?  The good thing about normalizing relations is that America will be able to assist the people of Vietnam, which is something American hade hoped to try and accomplish during the war.<br><br>
To Vietson,<br>
Thanks for takig time to post here and talk to us.  I enjoy hearing the Vietnamese and Amerasian viewpoint.  I hope you will remain here and continue talking with us.  Vietnam was a nightmare for us all, Vietnamese and American.  I hope you and your family are doing well here in America. You and your wife are a special part of America and I wish you best wishes and much good luck.  Keep telling you story, I would very much like to hear it!!!
